Preconditions:
The input grid must not be null.
The input grid must have at least one row and one column.
The input grid must only contain 0s and 1s, where 0 represents an empty cell and 1 represents a server.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the number of servers that communicate with any other server.
If there are no servers in the grid, the method should return The method should not modify the input grid.